The paper presents a local routing algorithm for graphs embedded on surfaces, which involves data structures and algorithms for graph theory (cs.DS) and networking (cs.NI). The algorithm also involves geometric concepts and techniques, such as homology bases and surface embeddings, which are relevant to computational geometry (cs.CG) and spatial information systems (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the theoretical implications of the algorithm for the efficiency of routing algorithms on surfaces, which relates to information theory (cs.IT).
